Orchestrates the three-phase lifecycle of a sandboxed cage run: prepare (validate billed modes, mint run dir, resolve runtime), run (stand up API proxy, exec via bwrap, collect exit code and diagnostics), and teardown (best-effort cleanup). Also loads `.cagevars` environment at bin startup before phase execution.

The `Resolved` struct bundles all inputs needed for one run: target project root, task ID, mode, absolute paths to three tools (ctx-verify, ctx-context, ctx-scan), dirty-tree permission, proxy log verbosity, and extra environment pairs from `.cagevars`. The `RunOutcome` struct captures the caged process's exit code plus an optional diagnostic string from proxy logging — both are opaque to the caller; diagnostics never alter the exit code (ADR-027).

`execute(r: &Resolved) -> Result<RunOutcome, CageError>` is the single entry point: it canonicalizes `target_root` to absolute form (required because bwrap binds it identically inside the cage; relative paths would create real directories on host disk instead of sandboxed mounts), runs prepare and run in sequence, and always calls teardown even on failure so crashed processes don't strand the run dir. Teardown errors are swallowed; only prepare and run errors propagate.